Magic material

Magic as a Physical Material:

Magic is a physical substance, capable of being concentrated into physical forms such as jewelry, clothing, and tattoos. It also exists naturally within the 7 Bodily elements, most notably in the blood, where it plays a vital role in enhancing biological and magical functions.

This magic material is essential to the operation of nearly all magical practices. Its presence allows for the infusion of magical effects into everyday objects, tools, or living bodies.

Properties:

  • Extremely Potent: Even trace amounts can generate powerful magical effects.
  • Microscopic Size: The particles of magic material are so small that a visible mass of it has never been observed in a single location.
  • Unstable Composition: Its full physical structure is largely unknown, and prolonged exposure to pure forms is considered dangerous.
  • Organic Affinity: It naturally binds to organic matter, especially the blood, making living organisms key carriers and manipulators of magic.

Applications:

  • Used in the creation of Glyph rules, enchanted weapons, and blood magic rituals.
  • Can be extracted or depleted, leading to Magic Deterioration of parent objects.
  • Embedded into tattoos or worn items for passive magical effects.
